
[1]ghost

   GHOST, n. [See Ghastly.]

   1. Spirit; the soul of man.

   In this sense seldom used. But hence,

   2. The soul of a deceased person; the soul or spirit separate from the
   body; an apparition.

   The mighty ghosts of our great Harrys rose.

    To give up the ghost, is to die; to yield up the breath or spirit; to
                                   expire.

        The Holy Ghost, is the third person in the adorable Trinity.

                       GHOST, v.i. To die; to expire.

                  GHOST, v.t. To haunt with an apparition.
